0).jpg|120px|Henk Nijboer]]\n| [[Henk Nijboer]] <br/> <small>(born 1983)</small>\n| Eighth Deputy Speaker\n| [[Labour Party (Netherlands)|PvdA]]\n| 5 June 2018 <br/> <small>({{Age in years and days|2018|06|05}})</small>\n| 20 September 2012 <br/> <small>({{Age in years and days|2012|09|20}})</small>\n|}\n\n==Parliamentary Committees==\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|- \n! Parliamentary Committee\n! Ministry\n! Jurisdiction\n! Current Chair\n|-\n| [[:nl:Vaste commissie voor Binnenlandse Zaken|Parliamentary committee for the Interior]]\n| [[Ministry of the Interior and Kingdom Relations|Ministry of the Interior <br/> and Kingdom Relations]]\n| [[Domestic policy]] \u2022 [[Civil service]] \u2022 [[Public administration]] \u2022 <br/> [[List of municipalities of the Netherlands|Local Government Affairs]] \u2022 [[Provinces of the Netherlands|Provincial Government Affairs]] \u2022 [[Elections in the Netherlands|Elections]]\n| [[Erik Ziengs]] ([[People's Party for Freedom and Democracy|VVD]])\n|- \n| [[:nl:Vaste commissie voor Buitenlandse Zaken|Parliamentary committee for Foreign Affairs]]\n| [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Netherlands)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]]\n| [[Foreign relations]] \u2022 [[Foreign policy]] \u2022 [[Benelux|Benelux Union]] \u2022 [[NATO]] \u2022 [[Diaspora]]\n| [[Pia Dijkstra]] ([[Democrats 66|D66]])\n|-\n| [[:nl:Vaste commissie voor Financi\u00ebn|Parliamentary committee for Finances]] \n| [[Ministry of Finance (Netherlands)|Ministry of Finance]]\n| [[Economic policy]] \u2022 [[Monetary policy]] \u2022 [[Fiscal policy]] \u2022 [[Tax policy]] \u2022 <br/> [[Financial market]] \u2022 [[Government budget]]\n| [[Anne Mulder]] ([[People's Party for Freedom and Democracy|VVD]])\n|-\n| Parliamentary committee for <br/> Justice and Security\n| [[Ministry of Justice and Security]]\n| [[Judiciary of the Netherlands|Justice system]] \u2022 [[Law enforcement in the Netherlands|Law enforcement]] \u2022 [[Public security]] \u2022 <br/> [[Emergency manageme