{"title_page": "Michael Wawuyo", "text_new": "{{short description|Ugandan actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Michael Wawuyo Sr\n| image              = \n| caption            =\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1948|11|11}}\n| birth_place        = \n| residence          = \n| citizenship        = [[Ugandan]]\n| education          = \n| occupation         = *Actor\n*Special effects artist\n| years_active       = 1991 \u2013 present\n| father             =   \n| children     = [[Michael Wawuyo Jr.]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Oluka |first1=Esther |title=The Wawuyos get their act together |url=https://www.monitor.co.ug/artsculture/Reviews/The-Wawuyos-get-their-act-together/691232-3787188-icbi20/index.html |website=Daily Monitor |accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref> <small><br> ''(Son)''<br /></small>\n| awards             = [[#Awards & Nominations|Full list]]\n}}\n\n'''Michael Wawuyo Sr''' is a Ugandan actor and special effects artist. He is notable for his big screen roles on [[Last King of Scotland]],<ref>{{cite web |author1=Kalungi Kabuye |title=Ugandans in the Last King of Scotland |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1171218/ugandans-king-scotland |website=New Vision |accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref> [[Kony: Order from Above]], [[The Only Son (2016 film)|The Only Son]], [[Sometimes in April]], [[The Mercy of the Jungle]] and small screen roles on NTV's [[Yat Madit]] and [[Power of Legacy]].\n\n==Career==\nWawuyo broke into the film scene when he played a terrorist soldier in a 1991 [[Mira Nair]] directed film [[Mississippi Masala]]. He went on to play mostly soldier roles such as an intelligence security officer in Black Blood, a military commander in a 2005 history-period [[HBO]] TV Movie  film [[Sometimes in April]] about the [[Rwandan genocide]] of 1994 and an air force commander in [[The Last King of Scotland (film)|The Last King of Scotland]], a 2016 Hollywood film about the former Ugandan president [[Idi Amin]].<ref>{{cite news |author1=Cyprian Musoke |title=Top Ugandan actors to star in Amin film |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1123724/ugandan-actors-star-amin-film |accessdate=5 March 2020 |agency=New Vision}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Okello |first1=Raphael |title=Uganda\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s star who has acted in four international movies |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1120969/uganda-eur-star-acted-international-movies |accessdate=9 November 2019 |agency=New Vision |publisher=New Vision}}</ref> He has also acted in many local and regional films like [[The Mercy of the Jungle]], [[Situka]], [[Kony: Order from Above]], [[The Only Son (2016 film)|The Only Son]] and The Boda Boda Thieves (Abaabi Ba Booda).\nHe debuted his television role as Achan, on NTV's [[Yat Madit]] in 2016. He then played Mr. Batte, the patriarch of the Batte family and the CEO of the family business in a 2019 television series [[Power of Legacy]]. \nHe also did work as a special effects and make up artist on films like Felista's Fable, for which he received his first nomination at the 2nd [[Africa Magic Viewers' Choice Awards]] in 2014, [[The Mercy of the Jungle]] in 2018 and [[Imbabazi: The Pardon]] of 2013.<ref>{{cite web |title=Uganda\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s star who has acted in four international movies |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1120969/uganda-eur-star-acted-international-movies |website=New Vision Uganda |accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2020\n| ''[[The Girl in the Yellow Jumper]]''\n| \n| April 2020 release\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Power of Legacy]]''\n| Zacharias Batte SR\n| 2019 ongoing television series\n|-\n|2018\n| ''[[The Mercy of the Jungle]]''\n| Village Chief\n| Rwandan film by [[Jo\u00ebl Karekezi]]\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Kony: Order from Above]]''\n| \n| About the [[Lord's Resistance Army|LRA]] Rebel leader [[Joseph Kony]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2016\n| [[Yat Madit]]\n| Achan\n| Aired on NTV Uganda from 2016-2017\n|-\n| ''[[The Only Son (2016 film)|The Only Son]]''\n| Dad\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2015\n| ''King of Darkness''\n| James - Airport store man\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Situka]]''\n|Muwadada\n|\n|-\n| ''The Boda Boda Thieves''\n| Goodman\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2014\n| ''Luzira:Escape From Uganda''\n| Inspector Michael Morais\n| [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]] thriller movie directed by [[Rajesh Nair]]\n|-\n| ''Bullion''\n| \n| Produced by Henry H. Ssali and directed by Phillip Luswata\n|-\n|2013\n| ''[[Imbabazi: The Pardon]]''\n| Kalisa\n|Rwandan film by [[Jo\u00ebl Karekezi]]\n|-\n|2012\n| ''Bye Bye Mzungu''\n| Waswa\n|Short\n|-\n|2006\n| ''[[The Last King of Scotland (film)|The Last King of Scotland]]''\n| Air Force Commander\n|Hollywood Production starring [[Forest Whitaker]] as [[Idi Amin]],  [[Kerry Washington]] as Kay Amin and [[James McAvoy]] as Dr. Nicholas Garrigan\n\n|-\n|2005\n| ''[[Sometimes in April]]''\n| RAF Soldier #8\n|[[HBO]] TV Movie about [[Rwandan genocide]] of 1994\n|-\n|1991\n| ''[[Mississippi Masala]]''\n| Soldier on Bus\n|[[Mira Nair]] directed film\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards & Nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Nominated work\n! Association\n! Category\n! Result\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2017\n| \n| [[Uganda Film Festival Awards]]\n| Judges' Choice Award\n| {{won}}\n| Honorary Award\n|-\n| 2014\n| Felista's Fable\n| [[Africa Magic Viewers' Choice Awards|Africa Magic Viewers' Choice Awards (AMVCAs)]]  \n| [[2014 Africa Magic Viewers Choice Awards|Make Up Artiste of the Year]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=Will Michael Wawuyo bring the Award home? |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1338382/michael-wawuyo-bring-award-home |website=New Vision Uganda |accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons}}\n* {{IMDb name|nm0915365|Michael Wawuyo}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wawuyo, Michael}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ugandan male actors]]\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ugandan actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Michael Wawuyo Sr\n| image              = \n| caption            =\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1948|11|11}}\n| birth_place        = \n| residence          = \n| citizenship        = [[Ugandan]]\n| education          = \n| occupation         = *Actor\n*Special effects artist\n| years_active       = 1991 \u2013 present\n| father             =   \n| children     = [[Michael Wawuyo Jr.]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Oluka |first1=Esther |title=The Wawuyos get their act together |url=https://www.monitor.co.ug/artsculture/Reviews/The-Wawuyos-get-their-act-together/691232-3787188-icbi20/index.html |website=Daily Monitor |accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref> <small><br> ''(Son)''<br /></small>\n| awards             = [[#Awards & Nominations|Full list]]\n}}\n\n'''Michael Wawuyo Sr''' is a Ugandan actor and special effects artist. He is notable for his big screen roles on [[Last King of Scotland]],<ref>{{cite web |author1=Kalungi Kabuye |title=Ugandans in the Last King of Scotland |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1171218/ugandans-king-scotland |website=New Vision |accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref> [[Kony: Order from Above]], [[The Only Son (2016 film)|The Only Son]], [[Sometimes in April]], [[The Mercy of the Jungle]] and small screen roles on NTV's [[Yat Madit]] and [[Power of Legacy]].\n\n==Career==\nWawuyo broke into the film scene when he played a terrorist soldier in a 1991 [[Mira Nair]] directed film [[Mississippi Masala]]. He went on to play mostly soldier roles such as an intelligence security officer in Black Blood, a military commander in a 2005 history-period [[HBO]] TV Movie  film [[Sometimes in April]] about the [[Rwandan genocide]] of 1994 and an air force commander in [[The Last King of Scotland (film)|The Last King of Scotland]], a 2016 Hollywood film about the former Ugandan president [[Idi Amin]].<ref>{{cite news |author1=Cyprian Musoke |title=Top Ugandan actors to star in Amin film |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1123724/ugandan-actors-star-amin-film |accessdate=5 March 2020 |agency=New Vision}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Okello |first1=Raphael |title=Uganda\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s star who has acted in four international movies |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1120969/uganda-eur-star-acted-international-movies |accessdate=9 November 2019 |agency=New Vision |publisher=New Vision}}</ref> He has also acted in many local and regional films like [[The Mercy of the Jungle]], [[Situka]], [[Kony: Order from Above]], [[The Only Son]] and The Boda Boda Thieves (Abaabi Ba Booda).\nHe debuted his television role as Achan, on NTV's [[Yat Madit]] in 2016. He then played Mr. Batte, the patriarch of the Batte family and the CEO of the family business in a 2019 television series [[Power of Legacy]]. \nHe also did work as a special effects and make up artist on films like Felista's Fable, for which he received his first nomination at the 2nd [[Africa Magic Viewers' Choice Awards]] in 2014, [[The Mercy of the Jungle]] in 2018 and [[Imbabazi: The Pardon]] of 2013.<ref>{{cite web |title=Uganda\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s star who has acted in four international movies |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1120969/uganda-eur-star-acted-international-movies |website=New Vision Uganda |accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2020\n| ''[[The Girl in the Yellow Jumper]]''\n| \n| April 2020 release\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Power of Legacy]]''\n| Zacharias Batte SR\n| 2019 ongoing television series\n|-\n|2018\n| ''[[The Mercy of the Jungle]]''\n| Village Chief\n| Rwandan film by [[Jo\u00ebl Karekezi]]\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Kony: Order from Above]]''\n| \n| About the [[Lord's Resistance Ar