mbed and sunk in the [[Gulf of Patras]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=Darmas>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?154907 |title=SS Darmas (+1941) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=21 December 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Frinton|1903|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Megalo Pefko]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|Greek destroyer|Hydra|D97|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Greece|royalnavy}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Freccia|destroyer|2}} was bombed and sunk in the [[Saronic Gulf]] by Luftwaffe Stuka dive bombers.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Ioannis Nomicos||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The coaster was bombed and sunk in the [[Gulf of Corinth]] off [[Rhion]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Messarya Nomikou||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Nafpaktos]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. Later salvaged by the Germans and repaired.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Miss Elaine||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The salvage vessel was bombed and sunk at [[Plymouth]], [[Devon]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. Raised on 14 May, repaired and returned to service.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Obra||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The coaster struck a mine and sank in the [[Baltic Sea]] off [[Griefswald, Rostock]], [[Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]].<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Pancration||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Milos]] by ''Luftwaffe'' aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=[[HMS Squirrel (1904)|''Sea-Serpent'']]\n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Battle of Greece]]: The [[yacht]] was bombed and 