eece|royalnavy}}\n|desc=World War II: The naval tugboat was sunk in Saronis Bay by Luftwaffe aircraft. Salvaged and put in German service as ''UJ-2106''.<ref name=\"Captured Greek submarine chasers\"/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==24 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=24 April 1941 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|Greek contraband chaser|A 4||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Greece|royalnavy}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|A 1|contraband chaser |2}} was lost on this date.<ref name=\"Navypedia\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/greece/gr_cf_a1.htm |title=A 1 contraband chasers, Hellenic Navy (Greece) |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=24 April 2016}}</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|Greek torpedo boat|Aigli||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Greece|royalnavy}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Alcyon|torpedo boat|2}} was scuttled in Saronis Bay.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/9922.html |title=RHS Aigli of the Royal Hellenic Navy |publisher=U Boat.net |accessdate=24 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_esc_ekwator.htm |title=Ekwator class patrol ship, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=24 April 2016}}</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|Greek torpedo boat|Alkyoni||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Greece|royalnavy}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Alcyon|torpedo boat|2}} was scuttled in Vouliagmeni Bay.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/9923.html |title=RHS Alkyoni of the Royal Hellenic Navy |publisher=U Boat.net |accessdate=24 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Andros|1914|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=([[File: Red Cross.png|40px]][[International Committee of the Red Cross|Red Cross]]): [[World War II]]: The hospital ship was bombed and sunk in the [[Gulf of Corinth]] off [[Loutraki]] by [[Luftwaffe]] aircraft with the loss of 3 lives.<ref name=NH044122/><ref name=Greek410424>{{cite web |url=http://warsailors.com/forum/archive/forum/read.php-1,33326,33330.html#msg-33330 |title=Greek losses 24 April 1941 |publisher=warsailors.com |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|Greek torpedo boat|Arethousa||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Greece|royalnavy}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Alcyon|torpedo boat|2}} was scuttled off [[Varkiza]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/9924.html |title=RHS Arethousa of the Royal Hellenic Navy |publisher=U Boat.net |accessdate=24 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|HMY|Calanthe}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The armed yacht was bombed and sunk off [[Milos]], Greece by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Cavallo||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and damaged at [[Nauplia]], Greece by Luftwaffe aircraft. She sank the next day.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Egeo||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[Lampedusa]] by {{HMS|Juno|F46|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=Egeo>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?137865 |title=MV Egeo (+1941) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=21 December 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Hellas|1893|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Piraeus]] by Luftwaffe aircraft with the loss of one life.<ref name=NH044122/><ref name=Greek410424/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Kehrea||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Bay of [[Frangolimano]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. There were no casualties.<ref name=NH044122/><ref name=Greek410424/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Kyriaki||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Suda Bay]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Manna||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The coaster was bombed and sunk at [[Aedipsos]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. There were no casualties.<ref name=NH044122/><ref name=Greek410424/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Petros|1892|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The coaster was bombed and sunk at [[Porto Heli]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. She was refloated by the Germans and scrapped at Piraeus. There were no casualties.<ref name=NH044122/><ref name=Greek410424/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Popi S||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Milos]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. Two crew and two passengers were killed.<ref name=NH044122/><ref name=GreekVol1/><ref name=Greek410424/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Pylaros|1920|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Galaxeidion]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. There were no casualties.<ref name=NH044122/><ref name=Greek410424/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Rover|N62|6}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Rainbow|submarine|2}} was bombed and damaged at Suda Bay by Luftwaffe aircraft and was beached. Later repaired and returned to service.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian destroyer|Simone Schiaffino||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Kingdom of Italy}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Rosolino Pilo|destroyer|2}} struck a mine and sank in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[Cape Bon]], [[French protectorate of Tunisia|Tunisia]].<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Spetsai|1904|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Gulf of Corinth off [[Psathopyrgos]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. There were no casualties.<ref name=NH044122/><ref name=Greek410424/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Ulster 