w.thomaslfriedman.com/worldisflat.htm The World Is Flat: A Brief History of the Twenty-First Century Thomas L. Friedman]\n*[http://www.cceia.org/viewMedia.php/prmTemplateID/8/prmID/5170 Three Billion New Capitalists by Clyde Prestowitz]\n*[http://www.cato.org/events/020422bf.html India Unbound: The Social and Economic Revolution from Independence to the Global Information Age by [[Gurcharan Das]] ({{ISBN|0-385-72074-2}})]\n*[http://www.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0470821949.html India: An Investor\u2019s Guide to the Next Economic Superpower by Aaron Chaze]\n*[https://www.vedamsbooks.com/no33605.htm Social Problems in India/B.K. Prasad] \n*Energy Crisis in India by M. G. Mehetre\n\n===Media===\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120328051336/http://mitworld.mit.edu/video/266 World is Flat, T. Friedman], Colloquim Recording at Massachusetts Institute of Technology.\n*[http://www.newstatesman.com/Economy/200601300017 One Land, two planets] (listen)\n\n===Websites===\n*[http://www.india-rising.com An information portal on India's rising status]\n\n{{International_power}}\n\n[[Category:Futures studies]]\n[[Category:21st century]]\n[[Category:States by power status]]\n[[Category:Superpowers]]\n[[Category:Military terminology]]\n", "name_user": "Bellowhead678", "label": "safe", "comment": "Colloquim->Colloquium -Fix a typo in one click", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India_as_an_emerging_superpower"}
{"title_page": "Vinny Troia", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vinny Troia\n| image              = \n| birth_name         = Vincenzo Troia<ref>{{cite web |title=The Cybersecurity Framework as an Effective Information Security Baseline: A Qualitative Exploration |url=https://search.proquest.com/openview/be7b0269c40e02ddb960aba7e6fc303e/1?pq-origsite=gscholar&cbl=18750&diss=y |website=[[ProQuest]] |language=en}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = August 21, 1980\n| birth_place        = [[New Jersey]], United States\n| citizenship        = American\n| education          = PhD (Information Security)\n| occupation         = Hacking Forensics Investigator, Cybersecurity speaker, Author\n| years_active       = 1997-present\n| organization       = Night Lion Security\n| website            = {{URL|vinnytroia.com}}\n| alma_mater         = [[Capella University]] (PhD)\n}}\n\n'''Vinny Troia''' is an Italian-American cybersecurity speaker, author, and hacking investigative researcher based in St. Louis, Missouri. <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.zdnet.com/article/a-hacker-has-wiped-defaced-more-than-15000-elasticsearch-servers/|title=A hacker has wiped, defaced more than 15,000 Elasticsearch servers|last=Cimpanu|first=Catalin|date=|website=[[ZDNet]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.livemint.com/technology/tech-news/a-billion-people-s-data-left-unprotected-on-google-cloud-server-11574451205399.html|title=A billion people's data left unprotected on Google cloud server|last=|first=|date=2019-11-23|website=[[Mint (newspaper)]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Mele|first=Christopher|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/01/technology/data-breaches.html|title=Data Breaches Keep Happening. So Why Don\u2019t You Do Something?|date=2018-08-01|work=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=2020-04-19|url-status=live|language=en-US|issn=}}</ref>\n\n\n== Early life and career ==\nTroia earned a PhD in Information Security and Assurance from Capella University for his qualitative research study investigating \"the perceived effectiveness of the [[NIST_Cybersecurity_Framework|CyberSecurity Framework]] among information security leaders\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://csrc.nist.gov/CSRC/media/Presentations/FISSEA-28th-Conference-Program/images-media/fissea_2015_program.pdf|title=28th Annual Conference \u201cChanges, Challenges, and Collaborations: Effective Cybersecurity Training\u201d|last=|first=|date=|website=csrc.nist.gov|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Musical Career ===\nTroia started his musical career in 2003. He has worked with numerous artists, including [[Jody Watley]], [[Dave Aud\u00e9]], [[Gareth Emery]] and [[Ultra Nat\u00e9]].\n\nIn 2004, Corbett and Troia remixed [[Ultra Nat\u00e9|Ultra Nate]]'s ''[[Free (Ultra Nat\u00e9 song)|Free]] on Curvve Recordings,'' which ranked #23 on the U.S. Billboard Dance charts.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|url=https://books.google.com.eg/books?id=nRMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA42&lpg=PA42&dq=ultra+nate+free+remixes+billboard&source=bl&ots=t4R3JKEzlW&sig=ACfU3U035dgf90T2Zb--LNO3RcaMxHWCug&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=snippet&q=vinny%20troia&f=false|title=Billboard|date=2004-10-23|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref> In 2005, he was the Executive Producer for the official remixes of ''[[Looking for a New Love]]'' by American dance-pop singer [[Jody Watley]]. The song ranked No. 1 on the Hot Dance Music/Club Play charts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/jody-watley/chart-history/dance-club-play-songs/song/480096|title=Jody Watley|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://classic.beatport.com/release/looking-for-a-new-love/2147|title=Looking For A New Love [Curvve]|last=LLC|first=[[Beatport]]|date=|website=Beatport|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> In 2006, his musical release of ''Flow'' with vocalist Jaidene Veda and remix by Gareth Emery rose to #24 on the Billboard Hot Dance Club Play charts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/dance-club-play-songs/2006-10-21|title=Dance Club Songs Chart|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Billboard (magazine)]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Troia and Jaidene Veda released their follow up record ''Do For Love'' with remix by [[Dave Aud\u00e9]], which climbed to #34 on Billboard Dance Club Songs chart.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|url=https://books.google.com.eg/books?id=WWxbO-SGG7AC&pg=RA12-PA57&lpg=RA12-PA57&dq=billboard+vinny+troia+dave+aude+remix&source=bl&ots=E-CO3FfG1C&sig=ACfU3U3lO-czLRXZYQxSFYb2Cm45lnjeYA&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=billboard%20vinny%20troia%20dave%20aude%20remix&f=false|title=Billboard|date=2010-07-03|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Computer security career ===\nTroia is credited with the discovery of several major data breaches including a database containing personal information of approximately 230 million Americans and 110 million companies belonged to ''[[Exactis]]'' in June 2018,<ref name=\"Wired1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/exactis-database-leak-340-million-records/|title=Exactis Leaked a Personal Info Database With 340 Million Records|last1=Greenberg|first1=Andy|website=[[Wired]]|accessdate=27 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Here's What It's Like to Accidentally Expose the Data of 230M People |url=https://www.wired.com/story/exactis-data-leak-fallout/ |work=[[Wired (magazine)]] |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/exactis-340-million-people-may-have-been-exposed-in-bigger-breach-than-equifax/|title=Exactis said to have exposed 340 million records in massive leak|last=Al-Heeti|first=Abrar|date=|website=[[CNET]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/cybercriminalite/article/2018/06/28/etats-unis-les-donnees-de-millions-de-personnes-et-d-entreprises-ont-fuite_5322635_5317654.html|title=Etats-Unis : les donn\u00e9es de millions de personnes et d\u2019entreprises ont fuit\u00e9|date=2018-06-28|work=[[Le Monde]]|access-date=2020-04-19|url-status=live|language=fr}}</ref> and unprotected Google Cloud server of 4 terabytes of personal data belonged to ''People Data Labs'' in October 2019.<ref name=\"Wired2\">{{Cite news|last1=Newman |first1=Lily |title=1.2 Billion Records Found Exposed Online in a Single Server |url=https://www.wired.com/story/billion-records-exposed-online/ |website=[[Wired]] |accessdate=22 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-11-22/a-billion-people-s-data-left-unprotected-on-google-cloud-server|title=A Billion People\u2019s Data Left Unprotected on Google Cloud Server|last1=Mehrotra|first1=Kartikay|date=|website=[[Bloomberg News]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.inc.com/jason-aten/an-enormous-data-breach-left-personal-information-of-12-billion-people-sitting-out-in-open.html|title=An Enormous Data Breach Left the Personal Information of Up to 1.2 Billion People Sitting Out in the Open|last=Aten|first=Jason|date=2019-11-25|website=[[Inc. (magazine)]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news |last1=Mathews |first1=Lee |title=Florida Marketing Firm Leaks Data On 200 Million-plus Americans |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/leemathews/2018/06/29/florida-marketing-firm-leaks-data-on-200-million-plus-americans/#5bffeb2d5435 |work=[[Forbes]] |language=en}}</ref>\n\nTroia is the founder of Night Lion Security, a cybersecurity services firm.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Zhong|first=Raymond|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/02/technology/china-xinjiang-app.html|title=China Snares Tourists\u2019 Phones in Surveillance Dragnet by Adding Secret App|date=2019-07-02|work=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=2020-04-19|url-status=live|language=en-US|issn=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketwatch.com/story/what-is-exactisand-how-could-it-have-the-data-of-nearly-every-american-2018-06-28|title=What is Exactis\u2014and how could it have leaked the data of nearly every American?|last=Paul|first=Kari|date=|website=[[MarketWatch]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> Before founding Night Lion Security, Troia worked as a security consultant for 8 years with the the US Department of Defense.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2016/07/06/why-the-state-department-is-so-bad-at-security.html|title=Why the State Department is so bad at security|last=Taylor|first=Harriet|date=2016-07-06|website=[[CNBC]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref> In 2017, Troia was hired by ''MGT Capital Investments'' to the Hacker Advisory Board, a cybersecurity company led by [[John McAfee]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/mgt-hires-gary-miliefsky-vinny-191349394.html|title=MGT Hires Gary Miliefsky And Vinny Troia To Tactical Advisory Boards|last=|first=|date=|website=Yahoo! Finance|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\n\n* ''[https://www.wiley.com/en-us/Hunting+Cyber+Criminals%3A+A+Hacker%27s+Guide+to+Online+Intelligence+Gathering+Tools+and+Techniques-p-9781119540991 Hunting Cyber Criminals: A Hacker's Guide to Online Intelligence Gathering Tools and Techniques.]'' [[Wiley (publisher)|Wiley]] Publishing. January 2020. P.  544. {{ISBN|1119540925}}.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*[https://search.proquest.com/openview/be7b0269c40e02ddb960aba7e6fc303e/1?pq-origsite=gscholar&cbl=18750&diss=y The Cybersecurity Framework as an Effective Information Security Baseline: A Qualitative Exploration]. Troia, Vincenzo. Capella University, ProQuest Dissertations Publishing, 2018. 10933040.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.vinnytroia.com/ Official website]\n* {{AllMusic | id= mn0000611578| title= Vinny Troia}}\n* {{Discogs artist|Vinny Troia|Vinny Troia}}\n\n[[Category:Living people|Living people]]\n[[Category:People associated with computer security]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vinny Troia\n| image              = \n| birth_name         = Vincenzo Troia<ref>{{cite web |title=The Cybersecurity Framework as an Effective Information Security Baseline: A Qualitative Exploration |url=https://search.proquest.com/openview/be7b0269c40e02ddb960aba7e6fc303e/1?pq-origsite=gscholar&cbl=18750&diss=y |website=[[ProQuest]] |language=en}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = August 21, 1980\n| birth_place        = [[New Jersey]], United States\n| citizenship        = American\n| education          = PhD (Information Security)\n| occupation         = Hacking Forensics Investigator, Cybersecurity speaker, Author\n| years_active       = 1997-present\n| organization       = Night Lion Security\n| website            = {{URL|vinnytroia.com}}\n| alma_mater         = [[Capella University]] (PhD)\n}}\n\n'''Vinny Troia''' is an Italian-American cybersecurity speaker, author, and hacking investigative researcher based in St. Louis, Missouri. <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.zdnet.com/article/a-hacker-has-wiped-defaced-more-than-15000-elasticsearch-servers/|title=A hacker has wiped, defaced more than 15,000 Elasticsearch servers|last=Cimpanu|first=Catalin|date=|website=[[ZDNet]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.livemint.com/technology/tech-news/a-billion-people-s-data-left-unprotected-on-google-cloud-server-11574451205399.html|title=A billion people's 