e-pop singer [[Jody Watley]]. The song ranked No. 1 on the Hot Dance Music/Club Play charts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/jody-watley/chart-history/dance-club-play-songs/song/480096|title=Jody Watley|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://classic.beatport.com/release/looking-for-a-new-love/2147|title=Looking For A New Love [Curvve]|last=LLC|first=[[Beatport]]|date=|website=Beatport|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> In 2006, his musical release of ''Flow'' with vocalist Jaidene Veda and remix by Gareth Emery rose to #24 on the Billboard Hot Dance Club Play charts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/dance-club-play-songs/2006-10-21|title=Dance Club Songs Chart|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Billboard (magazine)]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Troia and Jaidene Veda released their follow up record ''Do For Love'' with remix by [[Dave Aud\u00e9]], which climbed to #34 on Billboard Dance Club Songs chart.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|url=https://books.google.com.eg/books?id=WWxbO-SGG7AC&pg=RA12-PA57&lpg=RA12-PA57&dq=billboard+vinny+troia+dave+aude+remix&source=bl&ots=E-CO3FfG1C&sig=ACfU3U3lO-czLRXZYQxSFYb2Cm45lnjeYA&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=billboard%20vinny%20troia%20dave%20aude%20remix&f=false|title=Billboard|date=2010-07-03|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Computer security career ===\nTroia is credited with the discovery of several major data breaches including a database containing personal information of approx 230 million Americans and 110 million companies belonged to ''[[Exactis]]'' in June 2018,<ref name=\"Wired1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/exactis-database-leak-340-million-records/|title=Exactis Leaked a Personal Info Database With 340 Million Records|last1=Greenberg|first1=Andy|website=[[Wired]]|accessdate=27